'''ScotlandWhisky''', also known as the '''Scotch Whisky Tourism Initiative''', was launched in 2003 by [[Jim Wallace]] MSP, the then [[Deputy First Minister of Scotland]], and Ian Good, Chairman of the [[Scotch Whisky Association]].  The project is a partnership between the public and private sectors, with the aim of exploring where the [[tourism in Scotland|tourism]] and [[Scotch whisky]] industries can work together to realize mutual commercial benefits. It is financed by the Scotch Whisky Association, [[Scotch Whisky Experience|The Scotch Whisky Experience]], [[Scottish Enterprise]], [[Highlands and Islands Enterprise]], and [[VisitScotland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scottish-enterprise.com/whiskytourism |title=Whisky Tourism |publisher=Scottish Enterprise |accessdate= 2007-08-29}}</ref>

