'''Ski Mont Saint-Bruno''' is an alpine ski facility in the suburbs of [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]. It is located on the slopes of [[Mont Saint-Bruno]], in the city of [[Saint-Bruno-de-Montarville]]. It is located right next to [[Parc national du Mont-Saint-Bruno]], a Quebec [[provincial park]] that offers cross-country skiing and snowshoeing.<ref>http://www.sepaq.com/activites/sentiers_ski/ (accessed 27 March 2010)</ref><ref>{{fr icon}} Montreal Plus, [http://www.montrealplus.ca/montreal/venues/parc-national-du-mont-saint-bruno-fr "Parc national du Mont-Saint-Bruno"] (accessed 27 March 2010)</ref> The ski station is located on the South Shore of Montreal, 30 minutes from Downtown Montreal. The ski hill is 175m tall.<ref name=Gaz-2010-02-27/> It is also next to a quarry.<ref>{{fr icon}} LCN, [http://lcn.canoe.ca/lcn/infos/faitsdivers/archives/2004/12/20041213-144234.html "Une pluie de cailloux s'abat sur le mont Saint-Bruno!"], ''13 December 2004'' (accessed 27 March 2010)</ref>

The ski station was opened in 1965.<ref name=Gaz-2010-02-27/> As of the 2009-2010 season, the ski station has the largest ski school in Canada, with over 500 instructors, and over 32,000 students a year.<ref name=Gaz-2010-02-27>The Gazette (Montreal), [https://montrealgazette.com/sports/time+take+hills/2620281/story.html "It's time to take to the hills"]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, '''Rene Bruemmer''', ''27 February 2010'' (accessed 27 March 2010)</ref> The ski hill has 15 runs, and offers evening skiing on lit pistes.<ref name=Gaz-2010-02-27/> It also contains an isolation room to hold criminals.<ref>{{fr icon}} Le Journal de Montreal, [http://www.canoe.com/infos/societe/archives/2009/02/20090201-074406.html "Déjouer les voleurs"], ''1 February 2009'' (accessed 27 March 2010)</ref> It is considered an "urban resort" as opposed to a "destination resort".<ref>CanWest MediaWorks, [http://www.canada.com/montreal/montrealgazette/news/travel/story.html?id=7cdcbe5e-6a6a-4a0c-9f69-3f353f37ccf2 "Think small mountains for a great time"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108103218/http://www.canada.com/montreal/montrealgazette/news/travel/story.html?id=7cdcbe5e-6a6a-4a0c-9f69-3f353f37ccf2 |date=2012-11-08 }}, '''The Gazette (Montreal)''', ''20 November 2004'' (accessed 27 March 2010)</ref>

[[Ski MontJoye]] is owned by the same company that operates Ski Mont Saint-Bruno.<ref>{{fr icon}} La Tribune, [http://www.cyberpresse.ca/la-tribune/sherbrooke/200903/31/01-842165-montjoye-mont-st-bruno-le-plus-haut-soumissionnaire.php "Montjoye : Mont-St-Bruno le plus haut soumissionnaire"], '''René-Charles Quirion''', ''31 March 2009'' (accessed 27 March 2010)</ref>

